      %p Loans from other languages sometimes pass through Russian first. This is especially true of Church Slavonic, which Russian borrowed many religious terms from which were then in turn borrowed by Novegradian: #{t "воскрезати", "voskrezáti"} “resurrect”, #{t "соборе", "sobóre"} “cathedral”, #{t "Пасха", "Pashá"} “Pascha (Easter)”, #{t "вечерня", "večérnia"} “vespers”, #{t "иконостасе", "ikonostáse"} “ikonostasis”.

