                    "serve",
                    :arrow,
                    { :cyr => "служба", :lat => "slúźba" },
                    "service" ] ]
      = render 'derivation_table', :headers => headers, :words => words
      %p Verbs that form their perfective participles with -т- rather than -н- form gerundives with -кь- instead of -нь-: #{t "накрити", "nakríti"} “serve (a meal)” → #{t "накрикье", "nakríkje"} “course (of a meal)”.
      %p The suffix #{t "-ти", "-ti"} is a non-productive nominalizer historically related to the infinitive ending. Such nouns are often similar to or identical to the infinitives of the verbs from which they are derived. Verbs whose roots end in /k g/ take the suffix #{t "-кьи", "-kji"} as in the infinitive, but without the preceding glide.
      - words = [ [ { :cyr => "вѣcти", :lat => "vě́sti" },
