      %p The suffix #{t "-лньа", "-lnja"}, added to the past-tense stem of a verb, is similar to the above, but most commonly derives names of rooms. If the past tense is irregular, generally this form will be irregular as well (cf. ѣдалньа below, past tense ѣгле).
      - words = [ [ { :cyr => "кубати", :lat => "kubáti" },
