    = section "Nouns from Phrases" do
      %p The suffix #{t "-ка", "-ka"} is sometimes used to turn common multi-word expressions into a single noun. Such nouns tend to appear in the plural. Sometimes they are also limited to set expressions, as in the case of the second example below.
      - headers = [ "Phrase", "Meaning", :arrow, "Noun/Idiom", "Meaning" ]
      - words = [ [ { :cyr => "не вѣм", :lat => "ne vě́m" },
                    "I don't know",
                    :arrow,
                    { :cyr => "невѣмки", :lat => "nevě́mki" },
